frameDefinitions: This frame involves Buyers paying Money for Goods.

Commerce is a situation in which a Buyer and a Seller have agreed upon an exchange of Money and Goods (possibly after a negotiation), and then perform the exchange, optionally carrying it out with various kinds of direct payment or financing or the giving of change.
A Member is semi-permanently part of a socially constructed Group.
In this frame a Deformer deforms a Patient possibly against a Resistant_surface such that it undergoes a shape-change from its canonical or original shape into the Configuration, a new shape.
An Employer employs an Employee whose Position entails that the Employee perform certain Tasks in exchange for Compensation.
These are words describing a basic commercial transaction involving a Buyer and a Seller exchanging Money and Goods, taking the perspective of the Buyer.
frameExamples: I <t>paid</t> her $50 for a video game.
Victor is <t>part</t> of the Red Crescent
Ellen <t>crumpled</t> the paper into a ball.
I <t>employed</t> him as Chief Gardener for ten years.
Abby bought a car from Robin for $5,000.
